---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">The Renaissance title page</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene title-scene">
      <div class="iu__poster titlepage">
        <p class="tp__l1">THE</p>
        <h3 class="tp__head">ESSAYES</h3>
        <p class="tp__l2">or <i>Counsels, Civill &amp; Morall</i></p>
        <p class="tp__rule" aria-hidden="true">❧</p>
        <p class="tp__body">Written by the Honourable Author, and now<br/>newly set in the letter of <i>Claude Garamont.</i></p>
        <p class="tp__imprint">LONDON<br/>Printed in the Year M·DC·XXV</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </figure>

  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">The scholar’s page</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene16">
      <div class="iu__poster scholar">
        <div class="scholar__col">
          <p class="scholar__drop"><span>I</span>t is a happy accident of history that the most beautiful book types were cut not for beauty but for use. Garamont sought only a letter that would read clearly by candlelight.</p>
          <p>Four centuries on, the same proportions carry an argument across a screen with no candle in sight — proof that a good letter outlives its purpose.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scholar__col">
          <p class="scholar__marg">¶ De typographia</p>
          <p>The slanted stress, the small x-height, the bracketed serif: each a fossil of the broad-nib pen, preserved in steel and now in pixels.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </figure>
</div>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .scene16 { aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; }
  .title-scene { aspect-ratio: 3 / 4; max-width: 440px; }

  .titlepage { background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg); display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; text-align: center; padding: 7cqi 5cqi; gap: 2.5cqi; }
  .tp__l1 { font-size: 3.2cqi; letter-spacing: 0.3em; }
  .tp__head { font-size: 15cqi; line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: 0.02em; font-weight: 500; }
  .tp__l2 { font-size: 4cqi; }
  .tp__rule { color: var(--accent); font-size: 5cqi; margin: 1cqi 0; }
  .tp__body { font-size: 3cqi; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .tp__imprint { font-size: 2.8cqi; letter-spacing: 0.15em; margin-top: auto; color: var(--fg-2); }

  .scholar { background: var(--bg); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr; gap: 5cqi; padding: 5cqi; align-content: center; }
  .scholar__col { font-size: 2.6cqi; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .scholar__col p + p { margin-top: 1.4cqi; }
  .scholar__drop span { float: left; font-size: 11cqi; line-height: 0.74; padding-right: 1.4cqi; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }
  .scholar__marg { color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 1cqi; }
</style>
